.TH "pcie_flr" 9 "pcie_flr" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcie_flr \- initiate a PCIe function level reset
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pcie_flr
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device to reset
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initiate a function level reset on \fIdev\fP.  The caller should ensure the
device supports FLR before calling this function, e.g. by using the
\fBpcie_has_flr\fP helper.
